        </a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <span>© 2026 Longball Gazette · Longball-debug</span>
      <span>Hosted on GitHub Pages</span>
    </footer>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
```

You can tweak the issue titles, dates, and blurbs to better match your actual content, but the links (`href` and `onclick`) already point to the three HTML files in your repo plus the repo itself. [github](https://github.com/Longball-debug/Longfball-Newsletter)
